<?xml version="1.0" encoding="UTF-8"?>
<article desc="styling support">
   <meta desc="This article presents the support for SVG styling specification" />
   
   <title title="support for style attributes"/>
   The following style attributes elements are supported in the library
   <note>See <a href="https://www.w3.org/TR/SVG11/styling.html">Styling Effects</a></note>:
   <ul>
      <li>
         <code>fill</code>
      </li>
      <li>
         <code>stroke</code>
      </li>         
      <li>
         <code>stroke-width</code>
      </li>    
      <li>
         <code>stroke-dasharray</code>
      </li>         
      <li>
         <code>stroke-dashoffset</code>
      </li>   
      <li>
         <code>stroke-linejoin</code>
      </li>   
      <li>
         <code>stroke-linecap</code>
      </li>    
      <li>
         <code>stroke-miterlimit</code>
      </li>                             
      <li>
         <code>opacity</code>
      </li>                  
      <li>
         <code>style</code>
      </li>                           
      <li>
         <code>class</code>
      </li>        
      <li>
         <code>clipPath</code>
      </li>           
      <li>
         <code>filter</code>: see <ref id="filters support" />
      </li>                                                                  
   </ul>
   Note that the <code>opacity</code> and <code>transform</code> attributes are supported for all elements.
   
   <title title="support for styles specified within the style attribute"/>
   The following styles are supported within the <code>style</code> attribute:
   <ul>
      <li>
         <code>fill</code>
      </li>
      <li>
         <code>stroke</code>
      </li>         
      <li>
         <code>stroke-width</code>
      </li>    
      <li>
         <code>stroke-dasharray</code>
      </li>         
      <li>
         <code>stroke-dashoffset</code>
      </li>   
      <li>
         <code>stroke-linejoin</code>
      </li>   
      <li>
         <code>stroke-linecap</code>
      </li>    
      <li>
         <code>stroke-miterlimit</code>
      </li>                             
      <li>
         <code>opacity</code>
      </li>                        
      <li>
         <code>clipPath</code>
      </li>                                                                         
   </ul>   
   
   <title title="support for styles specified in the style element"/>
   The following styles are supported within the rules specified in the <code>style</code> element, and can be accessed
   through the <code>class</code> attribute:
   <ul>
      <li>
         <code>fill</code>
      </li>
      <li>
         <code>stroke</code>
      </li>         
      <li>
         <code>stroke-width</code>
      </li>    
      <li>
         <code>stroke-dasharray</code>
      </li>                                                                                 
   </ul>    
            
   <cat id="support" />
</article>
